menu "Application"

config APP_MATTER_ENABLE
    bool "Enable Matter protocol support"
    default y
    select BT_ENABLED
    select BT_NIMBLE_ENABLED
    help
        Enable the Matter (formerly CHIP) protocol stack.
        Provides 8 On/Off Plug-In Unit endpoints (digital outputs) and
        8 Contact Sensor endpoints (digital inputs) for home-automation
        controllers like Apple Home, Google Home, and Home Assistant.

        When enabled, the device advertises via BLE for commissioning and
        via mDNS (_matter._tcp) once commissioned. Commissioning state and
        fabric credentials are stored in the "fctry" NVS partition.

        Adds roughly 1.5 MB to flash usage and ~200 KB to RAM usage.

endmenu
